The problem sounds lke the primer is shrinking below the top
coat---causing the paint to look like spider webs, crows feet,
whatever----
And--here's another burr in the saddle---
Rust-O-leum, is not compatible with allot of other paints----it's the
fish oil in it that causes the problem.

Awful lot of work, to straighten this out---

You stuck now with that fish oil paint---

Let it set up and run over it with 600, then try again-----

Later,


Terry


 
